Arsenal’s unlikely Champions League tilt will have real momentum if they rack up a third consecutive win. It could make for a tense affair given that their season is, since losing in the Europa League Olympiakos, on something of a knife-edge and West Ham themselves desperately need points. David Moyes visits his one-time midfield maestro at Everton, Mikel Arteta, and will think a good performance at Anfield and resounding win over Southampton have formed a solid basis to trouble opponents who remain fragile. Nick Ames Saturday 3pm Venue Emirates Stadium Last season Arsenal 3 West Ham 1 Referee Martin Atkinson This season G24 Y69 R3 3.13 cards/game Odds H 4-7 A 5-1 D 7-2 Subs from Martínez, Maitland-Niles, Papastathopoulos, Mustafi, Holding, Willock, Guendouzi, Martinelli, Nelson, Lacazette Doubtful None Injured Soares (knee, 14 Mar), Tierney (match fitness, 14 Mar), Kolasinac (shoulder, Apr), Chambers (knee, Aug), Torreira (ankle, unknown) Suspended None Discipline Y64 R3 Form DDDDWW Leading scorer Aubameyang 17 Subs from Randolph, Martin, Balbuena, Zabaleta, Sánchez, Lanzini, Felipe Anderson, Ajeti, Snodgrass Doubtful None Injured Yarmolenko (thigh, 15 Mar), Soucek (thigh, 20 Mar), Fredericks (shoulder, Apr), Wilshere (hernia, May) Suspended None Discipline Y52 R1 Form LLDLLW Leading scorer Haller 7